Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_ptn_fplan_mode(25.10)                            set_ptn_fplan_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_ptn_fplan_mode  -  Sets  what floorplan objects will be written-out
       and/or read back in

Syntax
       set_ptn_fplan_mode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-export {macro | special_route | pin_constraint}}]

       [-import {macro | special_route | pin_constraint}}]

       Sets what floorplan objects will be written-out and/or  read  back  in.
       The   set_ptn_fplan_mode  command  allows  you to specify which objects
       should be written out during savePartition -fplan or read back in  dur-
       ing assembleDesign -fplan.

Parameters
       -export {macro | special_route | pin_constraint}
              Specifies the objects to be exported. This is used by saveParti-
              tion  -fplan  command to save the data to the fp file. Using the
              -export option, you can choose from saving macro and/or not sav-
              ing special_route data.

              Default: special_route (default data + special route  is  always
              saved)

              Data_type: enums={macro special_route pin_constraint}_list

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each set_ptn_fplan_mode  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

               man set_ptn_fplan_mode

       -import {macro | special_route | pin_constraint}
              Specifies  the  objects  to  be imported. This is used by assem-
              bleDesign -fplan command to load the data from the fp file.  Us-
              ing  the   -import  option,  you  can choose from bringing macro
              and/or special_route data.

              Default: By default, -import brings only defaults objects

              Data_type: enums={macro special_route pin_constraint}_list

       -reset Restores all parameters  modified  using  set_ptn_fplan_mode  to
              their  default  settings. The -reset parameter must be the first
              parameter specified. If you specify -reset by itself, the  soft-
              ware  resets  all  set_ptn_fplan_mode parametersto their default
              values. If you specify parameters after -reset, the software re-
              sets only those parameters to their default values.  Any  values
              that  do  not already match the default value and are reset will
              be reported.

Example
              * The following command will save only macro information.

                set_ptn_fplan_mode -export {macro}

              * The following command will reset  the  value  to  its  default
                value.

                set_ptn_fplan_mode -export -reset

